The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Business Briefs

 Mumbai, Sept. 27: The Multi Commodity Exchange of India (MCX) plans to enter the capital markets through an initial public offering to raise up to $75 million (Rs 335 crore). ?We will launch the offer after the regulatory approvals are in place,? MCX managing director Jignesh Shah said. Citigroup, DSP Merrill Lynch and Kotak Mahindra are merchant bankers for the issue.

 New Delhi, Sept. 27: The Insurance Regulatory and Development Authority (Irda) has recommended Rs 50 crore capital requirement for standalone health insurance companies, chairman C.S. Rao said. The ease in capital requirement, which is Rs 100 crore for life and general insurance companies, is aimed at promoting health insurance business.

 Mumbai, Sept. 27: The proposed scheme of amalgamation of Tata Infotech Ltd with Tata Consultancy Services (TCS) will be considered at separate meetings of unsecured creditors and shareholders of TCS on October 18.

 Calcutta, Sept. 27: The Jute Corporation of India will immediately release 2 lakh tonnes of raw jute at a negotiated price of Rs 1330 per quintal plus Rs 60 for freight to the mills to bring about a sobering effect on fibre prices and availability.

 Calcutta, Sept. 27: CESC has raised $40 million offering global depository shares to foreign investors, which concluded today.




